text: Baratili San Pietro (Boàtiri) is a town and comune (municipality) in the Province of Oristano in Sardinia, Italy. As of 2016, 1,312 people lived there. Its area is 6.1 km². It is 11 meters above sea level. == References == == Other websites == Category:Communes of the Province of Oristano
title: Baratili San Pietro
